# Disable package install/lifecycle scripts on `npm install` / `npm ci`.
#
# Suite-wide supply-chain hardening (mirrors prod-solid-server's .npmrc).
# Defends against a class of supply-chain malware that ships its payload in a
# postinstall / preinstall / prepare script that runs the moment the package is
# fetched (event-stream/flatmap-stream 2018, Shai-Hulud 2025-09).
#
# Verified on this repo's lockfile (2026-06-17): a clean
# `rm -rf node_modules && npm install` with this flag set, followed by
# `npm run lint` + `npm run typecheck` + `npm test` + `npm run build`, all pass.
# Nothing here needs a load-bearing install/lifecycle script:
#
#   - The @jeswr git deps (@jeswr/app-shell, @jeswr/solid-task-model) ship a
#     committed `dist/`, so they import with no build step under ignore-scripts.
#   - esbuild (transitive via vite/vitest): the binary ships in
#     @esbuild/<platform>-<arch> as an optionalDependency and loads at runtime;
#     its install script is not load-bearing.
#   - fsevents: native macOS file watcher, dev/optional transitive of vite;
#     disabling its script just falls chokidar back to polling (a dev-loop perf
#     hit, not a correctness issue).
#
# If a future bump introduces a dep that genuinely needs its install script to
# function, the failure is loud (the dep breaks at import) and the remediation
# is `npm rebuild --foreground-scripts <name>` in a controlled, reviewed step —
# not to lift this default.
ignore-scripts=true
